    watchFor: ["The denominator becomes P(B).", "Only outcomes inside B remain possible.", "A given B is not always the same as B given A."],
    commonMisconception: "Students may keep using the original total sample space. Conditional probability uses the condition as the new total.",
    teacherPrompt: "Ask: After we know B happened, what outcomes are still possible?",
